WEBVTT

1
00:00:26.375 --> 00:00:27.708
He loves that old camera.

2
00:00:27.792 --> 00:00:28.625
Come on. Yang.

3
00:00:29.917 --> 00:00:30.750
One second.

4
00:00:31.875 --> 00:00:33.375
Don't forget to join us.

5
00:00:34.000 --> 00:00:34.833
I will.

6
00:00:35.792 --> 00:00:37.125
Look here for a second.

7
00:00:39.542 --> 00:00:41.250
What are you doing? Come on.

8
00:00:41.875 --> 00:00:42.958
Come on. Gege.

9
00:01:00.375 --> 00:01:01.542
Yellow Equinox.

10
00:01:02.458 --> 00:01:03.667
Is that a new blend?

11
00:01:03.750 --> 00:01:04.750
I think so.

12
00:01:04.833 --> 00:01:07.625
I can make something close to it.
You know what kind of tea leaves?

13
00:01:07.708 --> 00:01:09.542
No. No. no. It's not this kind of tea.

14
00:01:09.625 --> 00:01:11.500
I'm looking for your crystallized teas.

15
00:01:12.583 --> 00:01:14.833
Sorry. I don't carry tea crystals.

16
00:01:15.375 --> 00:01:18.292
How can you be a tea shop
and not carry tea crystals?

17
00:01:18.708 --> 00:01:19.542
How frustrating.

18
00:01:20.167 --> 00:01:22.208
Let me make you something
that might be close.

19
00:01:22.292 --> 00:01:25.125
No. no. no. no.
No. this is… I have to go.

20
00:01:26.292 --> 00:01:27.417
Thanks for coming in.

21
00:01:38.625 --> 00:01:40.375
When's Daddy coming home?

22
00:01:41.167 --> 00:01:42.000
Soon.

23
00:01:42.958 --> 00:01:45.375
He's always late.

24
00:01:46.625 --> 00:01:49.292
Well. I'm late sometimes. too.

25
00:01:50.125 --> 00:01:53.917
And. you know. I've got a busy
few weeks coming up. so…

26
00:01:54.708 --> 00:01:57.000
I know. Yang will be here.

27
00:01:57.083 --> 00:01:58.333
So will Daddy.

28
00:01:59.208 --> 00:02:00.125
Mika.

29
00:02:01.958 --> 00:02:02.958
Mika.

30
00:02:03.958 --> 00:02:05.333
Don't be too hard on him.

31
00:02:06.167 --> 00:02:09.667
He told me there was a rush of customers
towards the end of the day.

32
00:02:09.750 --> 00:02:11.500
That's good news for Daddy.

33
00:02:12.083 --> 00:02:13.208
He needed that.

34
00:02:27.417 --> 00:02:28.417
I love that meal.

35
00:02:28.958 --> 00:02:30.917
Did you like the gochujang sauce?

36
00:02:31.375 --> 00:02:33.167
-I did.
-I made it.

37
00:02:33.250 --> 00:02:34.208
Imagine that.

38
00:02:34.292 --> 00:02:35.542
It was her first time.

39
00:02:36.458 --> 00:02:40.917
So you put the ingredients in the bowl
and you mixed them all together?

40
00:02:42.083 --> 00:02:42.917
Yeah.

41
00:02:43.833 --> 00:02:44.667
It's good. huh?

42
00:02:46.208 --> 00:02:47.625
It was really wonderful. mei mei.

43
00:02:48.083 --> 00:02:49.375
Thank you.

44
00:02:49.458 --> 00:02:52.875
Next time.
I'm going to Juliet the carrots.

45
00:02:52.958 --> 00:02:55.375
Julienne. and no. you're not.

46
00:03:11.333 --> 00:03:13.208
Mika's growing up so fast.

47
00:03:15.917 --> 00:03:18.375
She keeps asking why we're always busy.

48
00:03:20.583 --> 00:03:21.875
She understands.

49
00:03:22.417 --> 00:03:23.292
And Yang is--

50
00:03:23.375 --> 00:03:24.833
No. she doesn't.

51
00:03:28.250 --> 00:03:29.583
I feel like…

52
00:03:31.583 --> 00:03:32.958
I don't know. I…

53
00:03:36.125 --> 00:03:37.542
I don't want to regret.

54
00:03:38.583 --> 00:03:39.792
I'll make more time.

55
00:03:41.167 --> 00:03:42.083
I will.

56
00:03:43.417 --> 00:03:44.458
I promise.

57
00:03:45.667 --> 00:03:47.875
You know I'm not
putting this on you. right?

58
00:03:49.750 --> 00:03:50.625
Sort of.

59
00:03:50.708 --> 00:03:52.250
-I'm not.
-Teasing.

60
00:03:54.875 --> 00:03:57.417
I just want us to be a team.

61
00:03:59.500 --> 00:04:00.542
A family.

62
00:04:00.625 --> 00:04:02.042
Starting.

63
00:04:02.125 --> 00:04:03.625
Ignite.

64
00:04:03.708 --> 00:04:04.833
Starting.

65
00:04:04.917 --> 00:04:06.208
Reset.

66
00:04:06.833 --> 00:04:08.000
Starting.

67
00:04:08.083 --> 00:04:09.667
Ignite.

68
00:04:09.750 --> 00:04:10.875
Starting.

69
00:04:10.958 --> 00:04:12.167
Reset.

70
00:04:12.750 --> 00:04:14.208
Starting.

71
00:04:14.292 --> 00:04:15.667
Starting.

72
00:04:15.750 --> 00:04:16.833
Starting.

73
00:04:16.917 --> 00:04:18.208
Starting.

74
00:04:24.917 --> 00:04:29.250
Welcome. families of fours.
to our monthly dance off.

75
00:04:29.333 --> 00:04:33.125
We have over 30.000 families
competing tonight.

76
00:04:34.500 --> 00:04:35.792
Are you ready?

77
00:04:38.708 --> 00:04:39.958
Stay in sync.

78
00:04:42.708 --> 00:04:44.667
Precision points added.

79
00:04:50.667 --> 00:04:51.917
Take flight.

80
00:04:58.042 --> 00:04:59.375
Ready for combat.

81
00:05:03.000 --> 00:05:04.333
Fight time.

82
00:05:11.583 --> 00:05:13.333
Level one complete.

83
00:05:15.417 --> 00:05:18.042
3.000 families eliminated.

84
00:05:19.542 --> 00:05:20.708
Stay together.

85
00:05:22.167 --> 00:05:23.250
Steady.

86
00:05:28.125 --> 00:05:29.750
Sync bonus coming up.

87
00:05:43.333 --> 00:05:44.542
The hitchhiker.

88
00:05:45.333 --> 00:05:46.417
Go.

89
00:05:51.083 --> 00:05:52.458
Transition.

90
00:05:53.083 --> 00:05:54.875
Collect the TNT.

91
00:05:59.958 --> 00:06:01.167
Detonate.

92
00:06:07.167 --> 00:06:09.708
Smile. It's time for family portrait.

93
00:06:12.333 --> 00:06:13.542
Earthquake.

94
00:06:17.458 --> 00:06:18.667
Tornado time.

95
00:06:23.042 --> 00:06:24.667
Level two complete.

96
00:06:26.167 --> 00:06:28.833
9.000 families eliminated.

97
00:06:31.000 --> 00:06:32.333
Stamina round.

98
00:06:35.792 --> 00:06:36.792
Keep up.

99
00:06:38.583 --> 00:06:40.250
Stay in sync.

100
00:06:42.417 --> 00:06:43.250
Terminated.

101
00:06:44.667 --> 00:06:45.958
Babe! Babe!

102
00:06:46.042 --> 00:06:47.250
It wasn't me. It was…

103
00:06:48.500 --> 00:06:50.583
It wasn't me! Mika!

104
00:06:50.667 --> 00:06:52.250
Not me! It was Daddy!

105
00:06:53.208 --> 00:06:54.792
That's the furthest we've ever gone.

106
00:06:55.417 --> 00:06:56.333
That's true.

107
00:06:56.417 --> 00:06:58.167
Yang. we're out.

108
00:06:58.542 --> 00:07:00.042
Yang? Yang!

109
00:07:00.125 --> 00:07:01.208
-Yang!
-Yang?

110
00:07:20.250 --> 00:07:22.458
It looks like we have
three years left on the warranty.

111
00:07:22.542 --> 00:07:23.708
but they're not answering.

112
00:07:23.792 --> 00:07:24.875
Can't you just go there?

113
00:07:24.958 --> 00:07:27.542
I'm going to. I don't know
if the store is even there anymore.

114
00:07:27.625 --> 00:07:29.250
I did a search. I can't find them.

115
00:07:29.333 --> 00:07:32.125
-Did you call Brothers & Sisters?
-We didn't buy from them directly.

116
00:07:32.208 --> 00:07:33.583
They won't honor the warranty?

117
00:07:33.667 --> 00:07:35.583
No. the warranty is with Second Siblings.

118
00:07:38.958 --> 00:07:40.958
I told you we should've
just bought a new one.

119
00:07:41.042 --> 00:07:42.250
He was new.

120
00:07:42.917 --> 00:07:43.875
I mean. practically.

121
00:07:43.958 --> 00:07:44.917
He's refurbished.

122
00:07:45.292 --> 00:07:46.833
Certified refurbished.

123
00:07:46.917 --> 00:07:49.792
And he'd only been in use for five days.
Five days. And we saved--

124
00:07:49.875 --> 00:07:51.000
But now it--

125
00:07:51.625 --> 00:07:52.708
Nevermind.

126
00:07:53.208 --> 00:07:54.250
Let's just get him fixed.

127
00:07:54.708 --> 00:07:55.750
Yeah.

128
00:07:55.833 --> 00:07:57.125
You need to get Mika to school.

129
00:07:57.208 --> 00:07:59.042
Mika. come on. we need to go!

130
00:08:03.250 --> 00:08:04.167
Mika?

131
00:08:10.625 --> 00:08:12.542
-Mika?
-What happened to Yang?

132
00:08:15.125 --> 00:08:15.958
Hi.

133
00:08:17.667 --> 00:08:20.583
I don't know. He shut down last night.
He won't restart.

134
00:08:20.667 --> 00:08:22.375
-Has this happened before?
-No.

135
00:08:23.917 --> 00:08:25.083
You got a technician?

136
00:08:25.167 --> 00:08:26.208
He's still under warranty.

137
00:08:26.833 --> 00:08:29.542
I wouldn't take him back
to Brothers & Sisters.

138
00:08:29.625 --> 00:08:32.583
They're just going to try to get you
to recycle him for a new model.

139
00:08:32.667 --> 00:08:33.542
You know why.

140
00:08:33.625 --> 00:08:35.042
I'm not taking him there.

141
00:08:35.125 --> 00:08:36.625
The warranty's with another store.

142
00:08:37.417 --> 00:08:38.750
You didn't buy him direct?

143
00:08:39.708 --> 00:08:40.917
No.

144
00:08:41.000 --> 00:08:42.750
No. he's certified.

145
00:08:43.292 --> 00:08:44.708
I have to go and get Mika.

146
00:08:44.792 --> 00:08:46.375
Mika's still here?

147
00:08:46.458 --> 00:08:49.000
She didn't see Yang all dead-eyed?
I bet it freaked her out.

148
00:08:49.083 --> 00:08:51.875
-Yeah.
-Listen. I got a technician in Woodbury.

149
00:08:51.958 --> 00:08:54.833
It's worth the trek.
I'm going to send you his info.

150
00:08:54.917 --> 00:08:58.250
No. I'll just. I'll take him to Quick Fix
if I can't figure it out.

151
00:08:58.333 --> 00:09:00.375
That place is for morons.
Don't take him there.

152
00:09:00.458 --> 00:09:02.333
My guy will fix him
for a third of the cost.

153
00:09:03.208 --> 00:09:04.958
You tell Russ I sent ya.

154
00:09:05.042 --> 00:09:06.125
Okay.

155
00:09:06.208 --> 00:09:07.917
Okay. got to go. Thank you.

156
00:09:08.000 --> 00:09:08.958
Mika?

157
00:09:09.417 --> 00:09:10.250
Mika?

158
00:09:11.917 --> 00:09:13.625
Come on. kiddo. we got to boogie.

159
00:09:13.708 --> 00:09:15.542
I don't want to go to school.

160
00:09:15.625 --> 00:09:17.167
I want to be with Yang.

161
00:09:17.250 --> 00:09:19.583
Mika. the longer we wait.
the worse it's gonna be for Yang.

162
00:09:20.500 --> 00:09:21.875
What do you mean?

163
00:09:21.958 --> 00:09:23.250
He'll start decomposing.

164
00:09:24.333 --> 00:09:25.167
What?

165
00:09:25.708 --> 00:09:26.958
Come on. we got to go.

166
00:09:28.000 --> 00:09:29.292
Mika. now.

167
00:09:33.000 --> 00:09:35.292
FYI. Mika's going to be
with me for the day.

168
00:09:35.375 --> 00:09:36.208
Why?

169
00:09:36.625 --> 00:09:37.542
What happened?

170
00:09:37.625 --> 00:09:39.917
Well. you know. she just refused.

171
00:09:40.750 --> 00:09:43.042
-and I wasn't gonna drag her inside.
-Mika?

172
00:09:47.000 --> 00:09:48.000
Answer me.

173
00:09:48.750 --> 00:09:50.375
Mom. I can't.

174
00:09:51.083 --> 00:09:53.125
I want to be with Yang.

175
00:09:53.208 --> 00:09:56.208
It's okay. darling.
I just wanted to hear your voice.

176
00:09:56.292 --> 00:09:58.917
You need to listen to Dad
and be good and calm. okay?

177
00:09:59.000 --> 00:10:00.625
Is Yang going to be better?

178
00:10:00.708 --> 00:10:04.125
-Yes. he's gonna--
-Well. we don't know for sure. but…

179
00:10:04.208 --> 00:10:06.458
-What do you mean?
-Yeah. what do you mean?

180
00:10:07.125 --> 00:10:10.000
We can't make any promises.
but. Mika. listen.

181
00:10:10.083 --> 00:10:12.792
if you can be good and calm
for the rest of the day.

182
00:10:12.875 --> 00:10:14.583
I'm gonna bring you a surprise.

183
00:10:15.208 --> 00:10:16.042
What?

184
00:10:16.125 --> 00:10:17.833
You just promised her a surprise.

185
00:10:18.250 --> 00:10:19.708
-What is it. Mom?
-That's different.

186
00:10:19.792 --> 00:10:21.000
Mom. what is it?

187
00:10:21.083 --> 00:10:22.792
I wasn't trying to…

188
00:10:23.833 --> 00:10:25.542
I appreciate you taking the day off.

189
00:10:25.625 --> 00:10:26.708
Mom?

190
00:10:26.792 --> 00:10:28.792
Honey. be good and listen to Dad.

191
00:10:28.875 --> 00:10:31.875
I need to go. I have to get ready
for my presentation. We'll talk.

192
00:10:33.208 --> 00:10:35.167
What is she going to get me. Dad?

193
00:10:37.250 --> 00:10:38.417
I have no idea.

194
00:10:39.708 --> 00:10:40.917
I think I know.

195
00:10:42.625 --> 00:10:45.083
Just don't get your hopes up
for anything specific.

196
00:10:46.625 --> 00:10:49.500
Gege. I know what she's going to get me.

197
00:10:54.458 --> 00:10:55.417
Excuse me?

198
00:10:57.583 --> 00:10:58.625
Excuse me?

199
00:10:58.708 --> 00:10:59.917
Can I help you?

200
00:11:00.458 --> 00:11:01.792
Yeah. I was wondering if you--

201
00:11:01.875 --> 00:11:03.167
I purchased a…

202
00:11:03.958 --> 00:11:05.792
This used to be a store
where you could buy

203
00:11:05.875 --> 00:11:08.125
an older sibling for Chinese adoptions.

204
00:11:08.208 --> 00:11:09.792
It was called Second Siblings.

205
00:11:14.125 --> 00:11:15.875
We sell fish and tanks.

206
00:11:15.958 --> 00:11:18.375
Yeah. I can see. but do you know
what happened to that shop?

207
00:11:19.000 --> 00:11:21.500
Before my store. they sold memory.

208
00:11:22.208 --> 00:11:23.875
Memory-balia.

209
00:11:23.958 --> 00:11:25.958
Is that how you say it. memory-balia?

210
00:11:26.042 --> 00:11:27.000
Memorabilia.

211
00:11:27.083 --> 00:11:29.917
Memorabilia. Yeah. memories.

212
00:11:30.625 --> 00:11:31.667
But no technos?

213
00:11:32.500 --> 00:11:36.125
No. I'm not sure what it was before that.

214
00:11:36.708 --> 00:11:38.417
All right. thank you.

215
00:11:39.958 --> 00:11:40.917
Mika.

216
00:11:44.458 --> 00:11:46.792
Mika? Mika. come on. let's go.

217
00:11:49.333 --> 00:11:50.500
I want a fish.

218
00:11:55.125 --> 00:11:57.917
Gege? Meet Puffy.

219
00:12:01.833 --> 00:12:03.792
It's a black-box issue. okay?

220
00:12:03.875 --> 00:12:08.000
So. by law. we're not allowed to tamper
with the core interior. unfortunately.

221
00:12:08.083 --> 00:12:09.500
So what is it that you do here?

222
00:12:09.583 --> 00:12:12.292
Well. we are certified with
Brothers & Sisters Incorporated

223
00:12:12.375 --> 00:12:16.792
to repair or replace up to 12 parts
most commonly in need of service.

224
00:12:16.875 --> 00:12:18.833
If you want to take a gander there

225
00:12:18.917 --> 00:12:20.792
at the 12-point diagnostic.

226
00:12:20.875 --> 00:12:22.333
Yeah. but your diagnostics is just--

227
00:12:22.417 --> 00:12:25.292
Well. we hooked up Yang
to our certified analyzer.

228
00:12:25.375 --> 00:12:27.833
and all 12 parts were in working order.

229
00:12:27.917 --> 00:12:29.750
However. the readout did indicate that

230
00:12:29.833 --> 00:12:32.583
there was a core malfunction
unfortunately. so…

231
00:12:33.000 --> 00:12:35.417
So what? So. there's nothing you can do?

232
00:12:35.500 --> 00:12:37.583
There's a couple things we can do here.

233
00:12:37.667 --> 00:12:40.000
We could have him recycled
at Brothers & Sisters.

234
00:12:40.083 --> 00:12:43.083
If you do so before
he begins to decompose.

235
00:12:43.167 --> 00:12:46.042
you'll get $1.000 off on a new model.
which is great.

236
00:12:46.125 --> 00:12:49.000
If you don't want to have him recycled.
which I completely understand.

237
00:12:49.083 --> 00:12:52.083
we are equipped to turn
his head and his voice box

238
00:12:52.167 --> 00:12:53.792
into a virtual assistant.

239
00:12:53.875 --> 00:12:56.167
and we'd salvage
the remaining parts for ya.

240
00:12:56.250 --> 00:12:57.208
What?

241
00:12:57.292 --> 00:13:00.042
But we would have to send
the core to Brothers & Sisters.

242
00:13:00.125 --> 00:13:01.458
No. That's not gonna happen.

243
00:13:01.542 --> 00:13:03.667
Give him back to me.
and I'll get a second opinion.

244
00:13:03.750 --> 00:13:06.667
Sure. Of course. So. that will be
$250 for the diagnostics. please.

245
00:13:06.750 --> 00:13:07.833
You're kidding me.

246
00:13:09.500 --> 00:13:10.833
Unfortunately. no.

247
00:13:37.125 --> 00:13:38.833
That doesn't sound good.

248
00:13:38.917 --> 00:13:39.917
I know.

249
00:13:41.625 --> 00:13:43.083
What did you tell Mika?

250
00:13:43.167 --> 00:13:44.958
I said we were getting a second opinion.

251
00:13:45.542 --> 00:13:47.708
It's already taken longer than I expected.

252
00:13:48.542 --> 00:13:50.125
-Daddy?
-Hi. Mika.

253
00:13:50.708 --> 00:13:51.792
Hi.

254
00:13:51.875 --> 00:13:54.458
-Are you okay?
-No.

255
00:13:55.333 --> 00:13:56.542
I got a fish.

256
00:13:57.042 --> 00:13:58.208
You did?

257
00:13:59.000 --> 00:14:00.542
-She did?
-Yeah.

258
00:14:00.625 --> 00:14:04.375
Yeah. it's a little…
I'll explain later. We're almost there.

259
00:14:05.875 --> 00:14:08.250
All right. Keep me posted.

260
00:14:08.333 --> 00:14:10.250
-Okay.
-Bye. Mika.

261
00:14:11.083 --> 00:14:12.167
Bye.

262
00:14:12.833 --> 00:14:14.042
Say bye to Yang.

263
00:14:16.000 --> 00:14:17.125
Bye. Yang.

264
00:14:27.667 --> 00:14:29.583
It is an interior core problem.

265
00:14:30.708 --> 00:14:32.167
Yeah. we knew that already.

266
00:14:32.542 --> 00:14:35.500
I need your permission
to break open the core.

267
00:14:38.417 --> 00:14:39.583
It's against the law.

268
00:14:43.792 --> 00:14:46.667
It's just…
It's a bunch of corporate bullshit.

269
00:14:48.625 --> 00:14:51.667
You know who made that a law?
Brothers & Sisters.

270
00:14:52.500 --> 00:14:54.875
They're just trying to
protect their spyware.

271
00:14:55.625 --> 00:14:57.167
You recycle that.

272
00:14:57.875 --> 00:15:00.167
they will have so much data
on your family.

273
00:15:00.250 --> 00:15:01.792
it'll make your head spin.

274
00:15:02.542 --> 00:15:03.708
I'm not interested.

275
00:15:05.250 --> 00:15:06.083
It's your loss.

276
00:15:07.042 --> 00:15:08.458
You promised to fix him.

277
00:15:08.542 --> 00:15:09.708
Mika. I said wait outside.

278
00:15:09.792 --> 00:15:11.500
You said he was gonna be fine.

279
00:15:18.625 --> 00:15:19.708
Come on. man.

280
00:15:20.583 --> 00:15:22.042
You got to make a decision.

281
00:15:30.208 --> 00:15:31.708
Maybe this is a good thing.

282
00:15:32.375 --> 00:15:33.917
How is this a good thing?

283
00:15:36.375 --> 00:15:37.500
Yang has been…

284
00:15:38.250 --> 00:15:39.958
Yang has been wonderful…

285
00:15:41.500 --> 00:15:43.542
and we'd all miss him terribly.

286
00:15:45.375 --> 00:15:47.458
But we've been over-reliant on him.

287
00:15:50.125 --> 00:15:52.625
We bought Yang to connect Mika
to her Chinese heritage.

288
00:15:52.708 --> 00:15:54.292
Not to raise her.

289
00:15:54.375 --> 00:15:57.250
Yeah. but we spent a lot of money on Yang.
And I'm not gonna…

290
00:15:58.458 --> 00:16:02.833
feel bad if he does more for Mika
than teach her Chinese fun facts.

291
00:16:02.917 --> 00:16:06.167
He does a lot more than that.
but you're missing the point.

292
00:16:06.250 --> 00:16:07.292
What's the point?

293
00:16:08.833 --> 00:16:11.208
If we can't fix Yang.

294
00:16:11.292 --> 00:16:13.417
we're not gonna buy
another sibling for Mika.

295
00:16:15.833 --> 00:16:19.208
That would just be… strange.

296
00:16:21.250 --> 00:16:22.792
And we can't afford it anyway.

297
00:16:24.625 --> 00:16:26.917
So. we need to be more involved.

298
00:16:27.792 --> 00:16:29.375
More than we are now.

299
00:16:30.167 --> 00:16:32.458
And not just in raising her.

300
00:16:32.542 --> 00:16:35.625
in connecting Mika
to her culture and heritage.

301
00:16:35.708 --> 00:16:37.500
Like. that will be on us.

302
00:16:39.125 --> 00:16:41.833
So we need to be ready and willing.

303
00:17:57.542 --> 00:17:59.958
Mei mei. what's wrong?

304
00:18:00.417 --> 00:18:01.667
Nothing.

305
00:18:02.875 --> 00:18:05.208
Your face says something different.

306
00:18:07.500 --> 00:18:09.125
Just some kids.

307
00:18:10.417 --> 00:18:12.542
-In your class?
-No.

308
00:18:13.250 --> 00:18:14.833
Kids at recess.

309
00:18:14.917 --> 00:18:17.625
They were asking about my real parents.

310
00:18:18.542 --> 00:18:19.792
I see.

311
00:18:21.125 --> 00:18:22.958
And what did you say?

312
00:18:28.125 --> 00:18:33.667
I told them about Mom and Dad.
and they said. "No. your real parents."

313
00:18:34.583 --> 00:18:37.833
They said Mom and Dad
weren't really my parents.

314
00:18:37.917 --> 00:18:39.375
Not really.

315
00:18:40.292 --> 00:18:41.625
Do you believe them?

316
00:18:44.583 --> 00:18:48.208
I mean. they're our parents…

317
00:18:50.625 --> 00:18:51.958
but they're not…

318
00:18:53.083 --> 00:18:55.792
You know. they're not.

319
00:18:58.000 --> 00:18:59.417
Not really.

320
00:19:02.417 --> 00:19:03.250
Mei mei.

321
00:19:07.333 --> 00:19:08.500
Here it is.

322
00:19:09.750 --> 00:19:11.000
Take a look at this.

323
00:19:12.792 --> 00:19:14.542
Is the tree hurt?

324
00:19:15.292 --> 00:19:16.208
No.

325
00:19:16.875 --> 00:19:18.875
Something wonderful is happening here.

326
00:19:18.958 --> 00:19:19.792
What?

327
00:19:20.583 --> 00:19:23.792
You see.
this branch is from a different tree.

328
00:19:24.375 --> 00:19:25.500
It is?

329
00:19:26.167 --> 00:19:30.292
Yes. but now it's becoming
an actual part of this tree.

330
00:19:30.958 --> 00:19:34.417
Not really though. It's just pretend.

331
00:19:35.208 --> 00:19:36.417
Why do you say that?

332
00:19:36.500 --> 00:19:39.167
Because it's just taped to the tree.

333
00:19:41.417 --> 00:19:42.458
Right.

334
00:19:43.000 --> 00:19:44.500
It looks like that. doesn't it?

335
00:19:45.667 --> 00:19:48.667
Here. let's find one
that's already attached.

336
00:20:04.042 --> 00:20:05.208
Mei mei?

337
00:20:09.375 --> 00:20:10.708
See this branch?

338
00:20:11.417 --> 00:20:13.542
This branch is also from another tree.

339
00:20:14.333 --> 00:20:18.917
But look. you're connected to Mom and Dad
just like this branch.

340
00:20:19.958 --> 00:20:21.500
You're a part of the family tree.

341
00:20:22.250 --> 00:20:23.083
For real.

342
00:20:24.333 --> 00:20:26.750
Then so are you.

343
00:20:28.667 --> 00:20:30.208
Why do they do it?

344
00:20:30.292 --> 00:20:33.083
Why do they move branches
to different trees?

345
00:20:33.167 --> 00:20:36.375
It's called grafting.
They do it to make something new.

346
00:20:36.458 --> 00:20:39.917
Some of the apples you love were
produced by combining different trees.

347
00:20:40.000 --> 00:20:43.792
It's an ancient technique that was
used in China over 4.000 years ago.

348
00:20:43.875 --> 00:20:45.417
A Chinese fun fact?

349
00:20:45.500 --> 00:20:46.625
Yes.

350
00:20:46.708 --> 00:20:49.417
But you should know that
both trees are important.

351
00:20:50.625 --> 00:20:54.083
Not just this one.
but the one from this branch. too.

352
00:20:54.833 --> 00:20:57.958
Your other family tree is also
a vital part of who you are.

353
00:20:58.917 --> 00:21:00.083
Do you understand?

354
00:21:12.625 --> 00:21:13.833
I want to go with Dad.

355
00:21:13.917 --> 00:21:16.083
No. kiddo. you need to go to school today.

356
00:21:16.167 --> 00:21:19.625
But Yang! I want to see Yang!

357
00:21:19.708 --> 00:21:21.500
Hey. what about your pup-pup?

358
00:21:21.583 --> 00:21:23.375
Don't you want to show your friends?

359
00:21:23.458 --> 00:21:25.750
-Yang.
-Yang's gonna be home soon.

360
00:21:26.542 --> 00:21:27.625
Is he better?

361
00:21:28.250 --> 00:21:29.375
We'll see.

362
00:21:31.208 --> 00:21:32.750
But you need to go to school.

363
00:21:32.833 --> 00:21:35.083
Yang would want that. Do it for Gege.

364
00:21:37.458 --> 00:21:39.208
He'd want me to show my pup-pup?

365
00:21:39.792 --> 00:21:41.125
All right. I'm heading out.

366
00:21:41.208 --> 00:21:43.583
-Okay. Let me know how it goes.
-Will do.

367
00:21:46.000 --> 00:21:47.208
Your bag.

368
00:21:47.917 --> 00:21:49.083
Come on.

369
00:22:51.458 --> 00:22:56.208
We've always known that
some bots are equipped with spyware.

370
00:22:56.292 --> 00:22:57.625
Especially the foreign ones.

371
00:22:57.708 --> 00:22:59.125
And now we have proof.

372
00:23:00.292 --> 00:23:03.167
Now? So. you've never seen these before.

373
00:23:03.250 --> 00:23:05.458
What does it matter? It is what it is.

374
00:23:09.125 --> 00:23:11.000
-Have you looked at the recordings?
-No.

375
00:23:12.500 --> 00:23:15.375
-No! I'm pro-privacy.
-Can I see what's on here?

376
00:23:16.708 --> 00:23:18.208
You'll need a special reader.

377
00:23:18.292 --> 00:23:20.708
The connectors.
they're nothing I've seen before.

378
00:23:20.792 --> 00:23:23.542
This is some high-level shit. man.

379
00:23:27.042 --> 00:23:28.417
I mean. this is…

380
00:23:30.125 --> 00:23:33.458
Sorry. I'm just trying
to wrap my head around it.

381
00:23:37.958 --> 00:23:39.375
-It's disturbing.
-Yes.

382
00:23:42.208 --> 00:23:43.750
It is disturbing.

383
00:23:46.625 --> 00:23:48.375
It's time to wake up. man.

384
00:23:56.458 --> 00:24:00.667
So how do I buy a reader
that I can see what's on this?

385
00:24:01.542 --> 00:24:04.333
No one's selling a reader for that.

386
00:24:06.542 --> 00:24:09.875
You'll have to have one specifically
modified for those connectors.

387
00:24:10.958 --> 00:24:11.792
Great.

388
00:24:22.458 --> 00:24:25.542
Okay… I'm gonna give you a name.

389
00:24:26.917 --> 00:24:30.417
There's no number.
but this is where you find them.

390
00:24:47.292 --> 00:24:48.417
How much do I owe you?

391
00:24:50.375 --> 00:24:52.333
Like I said. I get paid to fix things.

392
00:24:54.792 --> 00:24:55.958
Thank you.

393
00:24:57.583 --> 00:24:59.208
I guess I'll take Yang back.

394
00:25:02.250 --> 00:25:03.333
I'll tell you what.

395
00:25:05.542 --> 00:25:08.167
Why don't you look at
what's on there first?

396
00:25:09.917 --> 00:25:13.500
If it's something bad. disturbing…

397
00:25:14.917 --> 00:25:17.833
you might not want this bot
in your house anymore.

398
00:25:21.292 --> 00:25:25.833
You can take him.
but also. he's gonna start decomposing.

399
00:25:27.292 --> 00:25:29.583
You won't get as much value for him.

400
00:25:31.167 --> 00:25:35.167
I can keep him hooked up on the simulator
until you know more.

401
00:25:40.042 --> 00:25:41.792
You're a friend of George. right?

402
00:25:43.042 --> 00:25:44.125
Yeah.

403
00:25:45.875 --> 00:25:49.542
Sorry. she's in a meeting.
but I'd be happy to pass on a message.

404
00:25:49.625 --> 00:25:51.292
Yeah. could you just tell her…

405
00:25:53.917 --> 00:25:55.917
Hello? Are you still there?

406
00:25:57.292 --> 00:26:00.042
You know what? It's all right.
I'll talk to her later.

407
00:26:00.125 --> 00:26:01.833
Great. Should I have her call you back?

408
00:26:01.917 --> 00:26:03.667
No. No. it's all right. Thank you.

409
00:26:16.667 --> 00:26:19.875
I was told I could talk to you.
I was looking for Max Walker.

410
00:26:19.958 --> 00:26:21.792
-but they mentioned--
-I'm not interested.

411
00:26:21.875 --> 00:26:23.000
Sorry?

412
00:26:23.083 --> 00:26:25.250
Are you here to talk some conspiracy shit?

413
00:26:26.375 --> 00:26:27.833
No. No. Russ told me that I could--

414
00:26:27.917 --> 00:26:31.417
Russ? Man. you're one of them.
I can't believe they let you back here.

415
00:26:31.500 --> 00:26:33.375
I'm not one of them. I…

416
00:26:36.042 --> 00:26:37.167
I have this.

417
00:26:38.667 --> 00:26:40.708
I was told Max might be able
to help me with it.

418
00:26:40.792 --> 00:26:41.625
What is that?

419
00:26:42.125 --> 00:26:43.583
Russ said it's spyware.

420
00:26:48.000 --> 00:26:49.500
Where did you find it?

421
00:26:50.958 --> 00:26:52.625
It was inside Yang.

422
00:26:54.625 --> 00:26:55.833
He's our…

423
00:26:57.500 --> 00:27:00.208
We bought him after we adopted
our daughter. She's Chinese.

424
00:27:01.250 --> 00:27:05.042
And my neighbor recommended Russ
after Yang shut down. and Russ broke in--

425
00:27:05.125 --> 00:27:07.292
Can I-- Sorry. Can I?

426
00:27:07.917 --> 00:27:09.000
Yeah. sure.

427
00:27:27.958 --> 00:27:30.708
Holy shit. this isn't spyware.

428
00:27:30.792 --> 00:27:32.875
I'm pretty sure it's a memory bank.

429
00:27:35.625 --> 00:27:40.042
The memory banks allowed the technos
to record a few seconds each day.

430
00:27:40.125 --> 00:27:44.667
The labs were trying to understand
what technos considered memorable.

431
00:27:44.750 --> 00:27:46.167
But the research was uncovered.

432
00:27:46.250 --> 00:27:50.833
the whole protect was shut down
immediately for violating privacy laws.

433
00:27:50.917 --> 00:27:52.000
So. what do I do?

434
00:27:55.792 --> 00:27:57.500
I'm not gonna lie. This…

435
00:27:58.250 --> 00:28:00.167
This is a big deal.

436
00:28:01.083 --> 00:28:03.708
If it's the regulator. then Russ is right.

437
00:28:03.792 --> 00:28:05.750
He's not gonna turn on.

438
00:28:06.417 --> 00:28:08.292
I'm just being honest with you.

439
00:28:10.375 --> 00:28:12.375
But his existence…

440
00:28:13.708 --> 00:28:18.625
Yang's existence would be an invaluable
contribution to this museum

441
00:28:18.708 --> 00:28:21.958
and just to the whole understanding
of techno-sapiens.

442
00:28:25.417 --> 00:28:28.542
So. I guess the real question's gonna be

443
00:28:28.625 --> 00:28:33.583
what do we pay you to have
Yang and his memories in our collection?

444
00:28:37.583 --> 00:28:39.333
Could I have another one of these. please?

445
00:28:51.500 --> 00:28:52.417
Answer call.

446
00:28:52.875 --> 00:28:55.000
-Hey.
-Hey. How's Mika?

447
00:28:55.458 --> 00:28:56.292
She's next door.

448
00:28:57.208 --> 00:28:58.875
Next door? At George's?

449
00:28:58.958 --> 00:29:01.000
-Yep.
-Why?

450
00:29:02.667 --> 00:29:04.875
Because you're not here.
and I have work to do.

451
00:29:06.042 --> 00:29:07.250
I'm taking care of Yang.

452
00:29:08.292 --> 00:29:10.708
