00:58:56.500 --> 00:58:58.375
-Look. I'm sorry if I've ever--
-Can I go now?

807
00:59:01.250 --> 00:59:03.417
Yes. Thank you. sweetheart.

808
00:59:09.250 --> 00:59:10.583
I'm really sorry. it's--

809
00:59:10.667 --> 00:59:12.375
No. it's… Honestly.

810
00:59:13.208 --> 00:59:15.917
You should see her fastball.
I mean. she's just.…

811
00:59:17.542 --> 00:59:19.542
Like. all day long. I mean…

812
00:59:21.458 --> 00:59:23.583
Well. thanks. George. I really have to…

813
00:59:24.250 --> 00:59:25.958
-Another time.
-Yeah.

814
00:59:26.750 --> 00:59:29.208
Hey. maybe we can get a drink together?

815
00:59:29.292 --> 00:59:30.333
Sometime?

816
00:59:30.417 --> 00:59:33.000
Yeah. Yeah. that'd be great.

817
00:59:49.125 --> 00:59:50.292
I want to see Gege.

818
00:59:52.583 --> 00:59:53.833
I know. love.

819
00:59:54.750 --> 00:59:55.833
You miss him.

820
00:59:56.708 --> 00:59:59.333
Me. too. We just can't see him now.

821
01:00:01.708 --> 01:00:03.542
What about the family dance?

822
01:00:04.458 --> 01:00:06.708
Are we never gonna dance again?

823
01:00:06.792 --> 01:00:08.417
Of course we will.

824
01:00:09.625 --> 01:00:13.875
But… we might have to
compete in the family of threes.

825
01:00:15.500 --> 01:00:17.792
I don't want to be a family of three!

826
01:00:17.875 --> 01:00:18.708
Mika.

827
01:00:19.125 --> 01:00:20.875
I want Gege back!

828
01:00:24.250 --> 01:00:26.708
Daddy's trying his best.
He's doing everything he can.

829
01:00:27.667 --> 01:00:28.917
I want him back. too.

830
01:00:32.583 --> 01:00:34.000
What about you. Mom?

831
01:00:34.667 --> 01:00:36.417
Do you want him back?

832
01:00:38.625 --> 01:00:39.667
Of course I do.

833
01:00:49.125 --> 01:00:51.125
This is dragging on too long.

834
01:00:53.125 --> 01:00:54.625
I just need a little more time.

835
01:00:55.250 --> 01:00:57.625
We need to start focusing on Mika.

836
01:00:58.500 --> 01:01:01.042
We're just making things
more difficult for her.

837
01:01:04.125 --> 01:01:05.167
Jake…

838
01:01:07.083 --> 01:01:08.292
do you hear me?

839
01:01:11.500 --> 01:01:15.833
If we can't get Yang fixed. we just…
We need to move forward. Okay?

840
01:01:15.917 --> 01:01:17.792
Now. Now.

841
01:01:19.375 --> 01:01:20.958
I need to tell you something.

842
01:01:41.333 --> 01:01:42.458
No. it's frozen.

843
01:01:42.542 --> 01:01:44.083
That's interesting.

844
01:01:44.167 --> 01:01:46.125
Try command "memory reveal info."

845
01:01:46.208 --> 01:01:48.125
and it should tell you
if it's corrupt or not.

846
01:01:48.208 --> 01:01:49.333
Okay. I'll do that.

847
01:01:49.417 --> 01:01:55.292
Also. I was wondering. is it possible
for cultural technos like Yang to…

848
01:01:56.708 --> 01:01:58.500
want to have romantic potential?

849
01:01:59.042 --> 01:02:00.750
You mean for humans to use them?

850
01:02:00.833 --> 01:02:04.875
No. no. no. I mean for Yang
to be interested in…

851
01:02:04.958 --> 01:02:08.292
There's a girl.
and she showed up in his memories .

852
01:02:08.375 --> 01:02:10.792
and. you know.
we didn't know anything about her.

853
01:02:10.875 --> 01:02:11.875
Really?

854
01:02:12.958 --> 01:02:14.250
That's fascinating.

855
01:02:14.333 --> 01:02:17.625
Because I've never heard of
cultural technos having that capacity.

856
01:02:17.708 --> 01:02:21.375
I cannot tell you how much
Yang and his memories--

857
01:02:21.458 --> 01:02:22.917
I should get that.

858
01:02:23.250 --> 01:02:25.542
All right. okay.
but we'll touch base soon?

859
01:02:25.625 --> 01:02:27.458
-Yeah. let's do that.
-Great.

860
01:02:33.542 --> 01:02:34.792
You've been looking for me?

861
01:02:35.917 --> 01:02:36.875
Yes.

862
01:02:38.208 --> 01:02:39.417
I'm Jake.

863
01:02:40.500 --> 01:02:41.583
I know.

864
01:02:42.542 --> 01:02:43.542
I'm Ada.

865
01:02:44.167 --> 01:02:45.000
Ada.

866
01:02:46.125 --> 01:02:47.500
Well. come in. Please.

867
01:02:48.333 --> 01:02:50.000
I knew something was wrong.

868
01:02:53.500 --> 01:02:56.417
We usually meet.
and he wasn't answering my messages.

869
01:02:59.833 --> 01:03:00.833
I'm sorry.

870
01:03:05.000 --> 01:03:06.208
I'm sorry.

871
01:03:08.208 --> 01:03:10.542
I know Yang loves
being a part of this family.

872
01:03:19.125 --> 01:03:20.375
Can I ask how you met?

873
01:03:22.042 --> 01:03:23.417
At the coffee shop.

874
01:03:25.542 --> 01:03:26.583
He approached you?

875
01:03:29.250 --> 01:03:31.208
He was a regular customer.

876
01:03:32.625 --> 01:03:35.542
He used to buy things all time.
which. you know. was funny

877
01:03:35.625 --> 01:03:37.250
when I found out he was a techno.

878
01:03:39.750 --> 01:03:41.542
But yeah. we started talking…

879
01:03:43.583 --> 01:03:46.208
and eventually he asked me
if wanted to do something.

880
01:03:48.250 --> 01:03:49.500
Were you and Yang…

881
01:03:50.625 --> 01:03:51.500
Were you guys…

882
01:04:02.250 --> 01:04:05.042
Well. we never really
talked about us in that way.

883
01:04:21.542 --> 01:04:24.292
Sorry. that's my wife. I need to…

884
01:04:25.292 --> 01:04:28.750
-Yeah.
-Sorry. Please. don't leave.

885
01:04:33.875 --> 01:04:36.417
She's freaking out.
You need to pick her up.

886
01:04:36.500 --> 01:04:37.333
What's she doing?

887
01:04:37.958 --> 01:04:40.583
She punched a kid.
then she started screaming at everyone.

888
01:04:40.667 --> 01:04:42.875
-Holy shit.
-Are you able to get her now?

889
01:04:43.375 --> 01:04:45.583
Yeah. Yeah. I'm on my way.

890
01:04:46.500 --> 01:04:47.333
Thank you.

891
01:04:50.292 --> 01:04:52.000
I want to see him.

892
01:04:57.583 --> 01:04:58.417
Mika…

893
01:05:01.333 --> 01:05:02.917
Yang loves you so much.

894
01:05:04.208 --> 01:05:05.917
He always talks about you.

895
01:05:30.458 --> 01:05:31.458
Thanks again for this.

896
01:05:31.542 --> 01:05:34.417
I understand.
I'm sure everyone misses him a lot.

897
01:05:38.125 --> 01:05:38.958
Mika.

898
01:05:45.833 --> 01:05:47.250
Gege.

899
01:05:51.292 --> 01:05:52.542
Gege.

900
01:05:53.792 --> 01:05:54.708
I'm sorry.

901
01:05:56.167 --> 01:05:57.042
Gege.

902
01:06:45.667 --> 01:06:47.583
He would have his own area.

903
01:06:50.875 --> 01:06:56.167
We could put some of
his memories on a loop…

904
01:06:57.667 --> 01:06:58.875
projected…

905
01:06:59.917 --> 01:07:04.000
or on a set of readers
that visitors could wear.

906
01:07:12.083 --> 01:07:15.875
Of course. any memory
would have to be approved by you.

907
01:08:17.875 --> 01:08:18.875
Yang.

908
01:08:50.625 --> 01:08:51.458
Play.

909
01:09:19.917 --> 01:09:21.333
Your collection is growing.

910
01:09:23.333 --> 01:09:24.458
Hi.

911
01:09:24.542 --> 01:09:26.000
Yes. it's getting bigger.

912
01:09:27.333 --> 01:09:29.292
Do you want me to stop now?
I can put some away.

913
01:09:29.375 --> 01:09:31.583
No. no. I'm not complaining.

914
01:09:32.875 --> 01:09:34.625
I like them quite a bit.

915
01:09:34.708 --> 01:09:36.333
Do you know butterflies were

916
01:09:36.417 --> 01:09:39.500
one of the favorite subjects of
Chinese trade art in the mid-1800s?

917
01:09:39.917 --> 01:09:41.500
No. I did not know that.

918
01:09:41.583 --> 01:09:43.958
The Chinese love butterflies.

919
01:09:44.958 --> 01:09:48.000
There's also a famous folk tale about
two lovers who die of broken hearts

920
01:09:48.083 --> 01:09:49.917
and reemerge as butterflies.

921
01:09:50.375 --> 01:09:53.667
Also. the ancient Chinese philosopher
Lao Tzu once said.

922
01:09:53.750 --> 01:09:58.292
"What the caterpillar calls the end.
the rest of the world calls a butterfly."

923
01:10:02.375 --> 01:10:03.333
I like that.

924
01:10:04.750 --> 01:10:05.792
I like that.

925
01:10:12.208 --> 01:10:13.750
Is this something you believe?

926
01:10:15.542 --> 01:10:16.792
That the end…

927
01:10:16.875 --> 01:10:20.417
…that the end is also a beginning?

928
01:10:20.500 --> 01:10:22.833
…is also the beginning?

929
01:10:26.917 --> 01:10:27.833
For the caterpillar…

930
01:10:28.292 --> 01:10:30.333
For the caterpillar. yes.

931
01:10:32.375 --> 01:10:34.458
But do you believe
it's true for all things?

932
01:10:38.292 --> 01:10:39.500
I don't know.

933
01:10:39.583 --> 01:10:42.833
I'm… not programmed
to believe in that way.

934
01:10:43.500 --> 01:10:44.708
What about you?

935
01:10:49.875 --> 01:10:51.417
I'd like to believe that.

936
01:10:52.167 --> 01:10:53.125
Do you?

937
01:10:54.375 --> 01:10:55.208
Do you?

938
01:10:59.542 --> 01:11:01.083
Sometimes I think…

939
01:11:02.750 --> 01:11:06.125
humans are programmed
to believe in such things. but…

940
01:11:10.375 --> 01:11:13.208
I don't know
if it's really in our best interest.

941
01:11:15.917 --> 01:11:17.792
May I be honest with you?

942
01:11:19.208 --> 01:11:20.042
Yes.

943
01:11:20.500 --> 01:11:21.750
Wait. is…

944
01:11:22.583 --> 01:11:24.542
Is not being honest an option for you?

945
01:11:25.000 --> 01:11:26.458
I don't think so.

946
01:11:33.917 --> 01:11:34.875
Go on.

947
01:11:40.333 --> 01:11:45.583
I'm fine… if there's nothing in the end.

948
01:11:50.417 --> 01:11:51.250
Are you?

949
01:11:54.000 --> 01:11:56.250
Maybe I was programmed this way as well.

950
01:12:08.708 --> 01:12:10.625
Does it ever make you feel sad?

951
01:12:19.500 --> 01:12:20.333
Well…

952
01:12:21.500 --> 01:12:24.792
there's no something…
without nothing.

953
01:12:35.875 --> 01:12:38.583
Does it ever make you feel sad?

954
01:12:39.292 --> 01:12:43.625
Well. there's no something…
without nothing.

955
01:12:45.250 --> 01:12:46.250
Lao Tzu?

956
01:12:47.875 --> 01:12:48.958
I'm not sure.

957
01:13:13.042 --> 01:13:15.458
Did Yang ever struggle
with being a techno?

958
01:13:20.417 --> 01:13:21.458
What do you mean?

959
01:13:22.917 --> 01:13:24.292
I mean. did he ever…

960
01:13:25.750 --> 01:13:26.917
want to be human?

961
01:13:32.167 --> 01:13:33.000
What?

962
01:13:35.167 --> 01:13:36.000
Nothing.

963
01:13:40.333 --> 01:13:44.083
It's just… that's such
a human thing to ask. isn't it?

964
01:13:45.333 --> 01:13:47.875
We always assume that other beings
would want to be human.

965
01:13:47.958 --> 01:13:49.583
What's so great about being human?

966
01:13:50.750 --> 01:13:53.333
So. he never struggled with it?
He never…

967
01:13:54.542 --> 01:13:55.625
questioned this?

968
01:13:59.417 --> 01:14:00.250
Not to me.

969
01:14:03.875 --> 01:14:04.833
I see.

970
01:14:13.083 --> 01:14:14.833
He did question if he was Chinese.

971
01:14:17.042 --> 01:14:17.875
He did?

972
01:14:20.542 --> 01:14:21.500
Yeah.

973
01:14:26.625 --> 01:14:29.042
What makes someone Asian?

974
01:14:32.375 --> 01:14:33.875
He'd ask that all the time.

975
01:14:36.458 --> 01:14:40.167
Maybe he just wanted to help Mika
understand what it means to be Chinese.

976
01:14:44.000 --> 01:14:46.125
He was dedicated to his little sister.

977
01:14:51.833 --> 01:14:53.625
Yeah. Yang was a good brother.

978
01:14:56.542 --> 01:14:58.500
He's a great brother.

979
01:16:46.833 --> 01:16:48.375
Reveal file info.

980
01:16:48.833 --> 01:16:51.250
Wrong command. Try again.

981
01:16:52.542 --> 01:16:55.458
Reveal… memory info.

982
01:16:55.833 --> 01:16:58.250
Access granted. Beta archive.

983
01:16:58.917 --> 01:17:00.208
Beta archive?

984
01:17:01.917 --> 01:17:02.750
Open.

985
01:17:02.833 --> 01:17:05.292
Wrong command. Try again.

986
01:17:05.375 --> 01:17:07.542
-Extract.
-Full command.

987
01:17:08.333 --> 01:17:09.167
Extract beta.

988
01:17:19.667 --> 01:17:20.500
Play all.

989
01:17:47.750 --> 01:17:48.583
Zoom in.

990
01:17:56.292 --> 01:17:57.125
Coordinates.

991
01:18:03.042 --> 01:18:05.542
-Hello.
-Hi. could I speak to the owners?

992
01:18:06.292 --> 01:18:07.500
Yes. One moment.

993
01:18:12.542 --> 01:18:15.042
He wasn't just quiet.

994
01:18:15.125 --> 01:18:17.292
He seemed despondent. Broken.

995
01:18:18.125 --> 01:18:19.792
We took him back a few days later.

996
01:18:19.875 --> 01:18:21.833
and they let us make an exchange.

997
01:18:21.917 --> 01:18:23.042
Brothers & Sisters?

998
01:18:23.125 --> 01:18:24.875
No. it was…

999
01:18:27.083 --> 01:18:29.208
Well. I can't remember the name.

1000
01:18:29.292 --> 01:18:30.875
We didn't buy him new.

1001
01:18:32.208 --> 01:18:33.042
You didn't?

1002
01:18:33.792 --> 01:18:35.250
No. but he was certified.

1003
01:18:36.875 --> 01:18:37.833
Second Siblings.

1004
01:18:38.833 --> 01:18:40.792
Maybe. Is that in Chinatown?

1005
01:18:40.875 --> 01:18:41.958
Yeah. it used to be.

1006
01:18:43.542 --> 01:18:47.083
I assume he was on
when you bought him in a… sleep state?

1007
01:18:48.042 --> 01:18:49.042
That sounds right.

1008
01:18:55.958 --> 01:18:56.792
Extract…

1009
01:18:58.875 --> 01:18:59.708
alpha.

1010
01:19:00.333 --> 01:19:02.208
There is not enough space.

1011
01:19:02.292 --> 01:19:05.500
Would you like to compress beta or gamma?

1012
01:19:05.583 --> 01:19:06.917
Compress beta.

1013
01:19:07.000 --> 01:19:08.208
Beta compressed.

1014
01:19:11.125 --> 01:19:12.417
Extract alpha.

1015
01:19:12.500 --> 01:19:14.500
There is not enough space.

1016
01:19:14.583 --> 01:19:17.000
Would you like to compress gamma?

1017
01:19:17.083 --> 01:19:18.333
Compress gamma.

1018
01:19:18.417 --> 01:19:20.542
Gamma is compressing.

1019
01:19:25.208 --> 01:19:26.417
Gamma compressed.

1020
01:19:38.750 --> 01:19:39.583
Extract alpha.

1021
01:20:07.333 --> 01:20:08.167
Di-di.

1022
01:20:34.458 --> 01:20:36.167
Di-di. wake up.

1023
01:20:37.333 --> 01:20:38.667
Di-di.

1024
01:20:42.500 --> 01:20:44.375
Is everything okay?

1025
01:21:20.167 --> 01:21:23.042
Hi. we're here to help Emma Davidson.

1026
01:21:23.958 --> 01:21:25.417
Yes. come in.

1027
01:21:29.833 --> 01:21:31.750
Slowly bring it down.

1028
01:21:32.458 --> 01:21:33.708
Side to side.

1029
01:21:35.208 --> 01:21:36.042
Good.

1030
01:21:41.125 --> 01:21:43.417
Your niece is going to like me.

1031
01:21:46.250 --> 01:21:48.375
Hey. Let's go get Yang.

1032
01:21:48.458 --> 01:21:49.875
Come here. Go get him.

1033
01:21:58.875 --> 01:22:00.250
Can I tell you something?

1034
01:22:14.708 --> 01:22:15.542
Come on!

1035
01:23:25.125 --> 01:23:26.500
She was my great aunt.

1036
01:23:27.833 --> 01:23:28.667
Your original?

1037
01:23:30.208 --> 01:23:31.333
So Yang knew her?

1038
01:23:32.458 --> 01:23:33.292
Yes.

1039
01:23:34.750 --> 01:23:36.333
He never told you?

1040
01:23:39.792 --> 01:23:40.667
No.

1041
01:23:43.958 --> 01:23:45.958
But I always… helped.

1042
01:23:51.542 --> 01:23:52.583
Sorry.

1043
01:24:06.333 --> 01:24:08.333
I wish he would have told me about her.

1044
01:24:09.042 --> 01:24:09.875
Us.

1045
01:24:10.958 --> 01:24:12.000
Do you?

1046
01:24:36.625 --> 01:24:37.875
He found you.

1047
01:25:43.500 --> 01:25:44.333
She's asleep.

1048
01:26:18.167 --> 01:26:20.708
I don't want Yang to be on display…

1049
01:26:20.792 --> 01:26:22.000
in the museum.

1050
01:26:23.958 --> 01:26:24.958
Neither do I.

1051
01:26:26.333 --> 01:26:27.417
But…

1052
01:26:29.208 --> 01:26:31.083
we should let them study his memories.

1053
01:26:34.750 --> 01:26:35.583
Do you think so?

1054
01:26:35.667 --> 01:26:37.417
Yes. His existence mattered.

1055
01:26:39.125 --> 01:26:40.500
And not just to us.

1056
01:26:47.250 --> 01:26:48.083
Yeah.

1057
01:27:01.958 --> 01:27:03.042
Come on.

1058
01:28:27.125 --> 01:28:28.125
Gege.

1059
01:28:29.125 --> 01:28:30.583
I want to thank you

1060
01:28:31.292 --> 01:28:34.792
for being the best big brother
in the world.

1061
01:28:35.875 --> 01:28:37.125
I'm sorry.

1062
01:28:38.208 --> 01:28:40.125
I shouldn't have said that I hated you.

1063
01:28:41.583 --> 01:28:43.667
I miss you. big brother.

1064
01:28:54.958 --> 01:28:55.792
Daddy.

1065
01:28:56.958 --> 01:28:58.417
Hey. what are you doing up?

1066
01:28:59.500 --> 01:29:00.792
What are you doing?

1067
01:29:03.000 --> 01:29:04.125
You want some water?

1068
01:29:06.292 --> 01:29:07.750
Want to sit beside me?

1069
01:29:19.667 --> 01:29:20.792
Can't sleep.

1070
01:29:22.333 --> 01:29:23.167
Me neither.

1071
01:29:25.750 --> 01:29:27.542
Don't want to say bye to Gege.

1072
01:29:29.250 --> 01:29:30.083
Me neither.

1073
01:29:36.250 --> 01:29:39.458
I wanna be

1074
01:29:42.500 --> 01:29:45.708
I wanna be

1075
01:29:47.917 --> 01:29:53.500
I wanna be just like a melody

1076
01:29:53.583 --> 01:29:57.167
Just like a simple sound

1077
01:29:57.250 --> 01:30:00.500
Like a harmony
